g aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529738\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104luh1665702748423.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/luh1665702748423.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/luh1665702748423.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"luh1665702748423\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To uninstall the RMS License Manager, use the uninstall script that was created in the directory you specified during installation. You will be asked to return your license so that you can use it on a different machine.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"luh1665702748423__context_w2365ab1b5b1_w2366ab1b5_w2367ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"luh1665702748423__p_d67697e1_d67698e1_d67699e1\">Returning the license allows you to move your RMS License Manager to a different machine and reuse the license. This feature is also useful if you wish to change from a cloud-served license to a license file. If you are returning a cloud-served license, you will need to have the Entitlement ID for the license you are returning.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"luh1665702748423__p_d67700e1_d67701e1_d67702e1\">To uninstall:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"luh1665702748423__li_d30476e1_d30477e1_d30478e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Run the <span class=\"ph filepath\">uninstallrms.sh</span> script or select the uninstall script option in upgrade mode (see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mjb1665702748492.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mjb1665702748492.html\" title=\"Use the installation script to update or upgrade an older version of the RMS License Manager and the Cloud Plug-in, or to switch license type from a cloud-served license to a license file or license code (or vice versa).\">Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux</a>).\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"luh1665702748423__li_d30479e1_d30480e1_d30481e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"luh1665702748423__p_d67703e1_d67704e1_d67705e1\">At the first prompt, press\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Enter</span> to continue with the uninstall or <code class=\"ph codeph\">q</code>\n               to exit. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup stepresult\">The uninstall script now proceeds to stop and remove the RMS\n               service.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"luh1665702748423__li_d30482e1_d30483e1_d30484e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If a cloud-served license is detected, you are prompted to enter the Entitlement ID of the license you are returning. Enter your Entitlement ID and press <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Enter</span>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"luh1665702748423__li_d30485e1_d30486e1_d30487e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"luh1665702748423__p_d67706e1_d67707e1_d67708e1\">Enter an additional Entitlement ID, if applicable, or press <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Enter</span> to continue. You can return multiple Entitlement IDs.\n The script now proceeds to return your license(s). This can take up to 3 minutes per license. Do not stop the script during this process.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"luh1665702748423__li_d30488e1_d30489e1_d30490e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">When prompted, choose to remove all files in your installation directory<span class=\"ph\">, including Cloud Plug-in configuration\n                  files</span>. Select yes (<code class=\"ph codeph\">y</code>) to remove them or no\n                  (<code class=\"ph codeph\">n</code>) to keep them. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"luh1665702748423__note_w2371ab1b5b3b9b3b1_w2372ab1b5b3b9b3_w2373ab1b5b3b9_w2374ab1b5b3_w2375ab1b5_w2376ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If a license file is detected, this will also be deleted. You can\n                  select (<code class=\"ph codeph\">n</code>) or quit the process to make a copy of the file before\n                  continuing. Alternatively, you can download a new license file from the Sentinel\n                  EMS Customer Portal.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"luh1665702748423__p_d67709e1_d67710e1_d67711e1\">The uninstall script now removes the files and\n                  exits.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"luh1665702748423__result_w2368ab1b5b5_w2369ab1b5_w2370ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"luh1665702748423__p_d67712e1_d67713e1_d67714e1\">To remove your RMS License Manager installation manually:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"luh1665702748423__li_d30491e1_d30492e1_d30493e1\">Stop and disable the <span class=\"ph filepath\">rms</span> service.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"luh1665702748423__li_d30494e1_d30495e1_d30496e1\">Remove the <span class=\"ph filepath\">rms</span> script in <span class=\"ph filepath\">/etc/init.d</span>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"luh1665702748423__li_d30497e1_d30498e1_d30499e1\">Remove your installation directory:\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"luh1665702748423__p_d67715e1_d67716e1_d67717e1\">\n<kbd class=\"ph userinput\">rm -rf <var class=\"keyword varname\">InstallationDirectory</var>\n</kbd>\n</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529738\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529738\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix To uninstall the RMS License Manager, use the uninstall script that was created in the directory you specified during installation. You will be asked to return your license so that you can use it on a different machine. Returning the license allows you to move your RMS License Manager to a different machine and reuse the license. This feature is also useful if you wish to change from a cloud-served license to a license file. If you are returning a cloud-served license, you will need to have the Entitlement ID for the license you are returning. To uninstall: Run the uninstallrms.sh script or select the uninstall script option in upgrade mode (see Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux ). At the first prompt, press Enter to continue with the uninstall or q to exit. The uninstall script now proceeds to stop and remove the RMS service. If a cloud-served license is detected, you are prompted to enter the Entitlement ID of the license you are returning. Enter your Entitlement ID and press Enter . Enter an additional Entitlement ID, if applicable, or press Enter to continue. You can return multiple Entitlement IDs. The script now proceeds to return your license(s). This can take up to 3 minutes per license. Do not stop the script during this process. When prompted, choose to remove all files in your installation directory , including Cloud Plug-in configuration files . Select yes ( y ) to remove them or no ( n ) to keep them. Note: If a license file is detected, this will also be deleted. You can select ( n ) or quit the process to make a copy of the file before continuing. Alternatively, you can download a new license file from the Sentinel EMS Customer Portal. The uninstall script now removes the files and exits. To remove your RMS License Manager installation manually: Stop and disable the rms service. Remove the rms script in /etc/init.d . Remove your installation directory: rm -rf InstallationDirectory Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}